# kriegerdataforge-cicd — Cursor Rules

## Purpose

This is the **shared reusable GitHub Actions workflow library** for the KriegerDataForge
ecosystem. All deployment logic lives here. Consumer repos call these workflows rather
than maintaining their own deploy pipelines.

## Implemented Workflows

| File | Purpose | Consumers |
|---|---|---|
| `cd-nextjs-vercel.yml` | Deploy Next.js → Vercel | `fitness-app-frontend`, `tiffanys-space`, `arthurs-portfolio` |
| `cd-python-vercel.yml` | Deploy FastAPI → Vercel + Alembic migrations | `kriegerdataforge`, `fitness-app-backend`, `tiffanys-space-backend` |
| `cd-terraform.yml` | `terraform plan` + `apply` | `kriegerdataforge-terraform` |
| `issue-create-repo.yml` | Auto-provision new repos from issue template | internal |

See `docs/WORKFLOWS.md` for full calling syntax, inputs, and secrets for each workflow.

## Deployment Model

- **All deploys are manual** (`workflow_dispatch` only — no auto-deploy on push)
- **Vercel git auto-deploy is disabled** in Terraform (`git_deployment = false`)
- Every deploy passes through a **GitHub Environment gate**: workflow pauses for required reviewer approval before secrets are loaded and deploy runs
- `VERCEL_TOKEN`, `DB_DATABASE_URL`, and all credentials live **only** in GitHub Environment secrets—never in `.env` files, never in code, never in logs

## Environment Approval Model

| Environment | Who can approve | Branch |
|---|---|---|
| `dev` | Owner + collaborators | `main` only |
| `prod` | Owner only | `main` only |
| `infra` | Owner only | `main` only |

> Environment names are ALWAYS `dev`/`prod`/`infra` — NEVER `development`/`production`/`infrastructure`.

## GitHub Actions Rules

- Every deployment workflow MUST use `environment:` to activate the GitHub Environment gate
- Pin all third-party action versions to a tag (e.g. `@v6`) — never `@main` or `@latest`
- `secrets: inherit` is the standard pattern for passing environment secrets from a caller workflow to a reusable workflow
- Never log secrets — even masked secrets should not appear in `echo` or debug steps
- Keep steps atomic — each step does one thing
- `id-token: write` is required for Vercel OIDC in deploy workflows

## Security Rules

- Use `${{ secrets.NAME }}` for all credentials — never hardcode
- Set minimum required `permissions:` on every workflow
- Never use `pull_request_target` with an untrusted code checkout
- Use `environment:` for all production and deployment jobs

## Backward Compatibility Rules

- Adding `required: true` to an existing input = **breaking change** for all consumers
- Removing or renaming `outputs:` = breaking change
- Adding new required `secrets:` = breaking change
- When in doubt, add a new workflow rather than modifying an existing one
- Any change here may affect 5 consumer repos — coordinate or add a new workflow

## Repo Structure

- `.github/workflows/` — reusable workflows (all have `workflow_call:` trigger)
- `docs/WORKFLOWS.md` — full workflow catalog and consumer integration guide
- `docs/MANUAL_SETUP.md` — environment setup, secrets, PAT configuration

See `CLAUDE.md` for full project context.

## Security — read [`skills.md`](./skills.md)

This repo follows the KriegerDataForge ecosystem **security playbook** in [`skills.md`](./skills.md).
**Before any security-sensitive work** — auth/OIDC/tokens, BFF/proxy/CSP/cookies, backend authz/endpoints,
secrets/env/config, Terraform/infra, CI/CD, or dependencies — open `skills.md` and follow the **scenario**
that matches your task.

Non-negotiables (full detail + the scenario rules are in `skills.md`):

- **Fail closed, never open.** The **server is authoritative** — recompute security/$-relevant values
  (totals, prices, roles, status); never trust client-sent ones.
- **Never trust client input** for a security decision — IPs (use the edge header, not raw `X-Forwarded-For`),
  hostnames / `request.url` (the internal bind, not the browser host), `Origin`, ownership (exact check, not a
  substring/regex).
- **Secrets never touch git or logs** — real values only in gitignored files; `.example` holds placeholders;
  never echo a secret; the owner rotates.
- **Least privilege** — closed request schemas + field allow-lists (no blind `setattr`), distinct per-client
  OIDC audiences, validated `iss`/`aud`.
- Found a security issue? **Verify it's real, then flag it** — and **pause for owner approval before any
  architectural, destructive, or behavior-changing edit** (OIDC protocol changes get a design note first).
